div1.p:
Now, at this day, comes the above named plaintiff by Mr. John H. Hal, United States Attorney, and the defendants
       herein thier own proper person, and thereupon, said plaintiff moves the Court for judgment upon the verdict rendered
       herein, against said defendants;

Whereupon, It is Considered, that each of said defendants be imprisoned at hard labor, for the term of his natural life;
       and It Is Ordered that, until otheriwse ordered or decided, said defendents be committed to the Oregon State Penitentiary,
       at Salem, Oregon, until said sentence of confinement be performed, or until they be discharged according to law.
